from folium.plugins import MarkerCluster
import pandas as pd
import folium


GTA_COORDINATES = (43.5890, -79.6441)
lakeinfo=pd.read_csv('/Users/Steven/Desktop/Project 1/project.csv', sep=',', encoding='latin1')

Lakenumbers = 669


lake_location=lakeinfo['Coords']
lake_location=lake_location.tolist()
j=0
for i in lake_location:
    if j < len(lake_location):
        lake_location[j]=tuple(map(float,i.split(',')))
        j+=1
lakeinfo['Coords']=lake_location

da=lakeinfo.to_dict('records')
info_box_template = """
<dl>
<dt>Lake Name</dt><dd>{Lake Name}</dd>
<dt>Municipality</dt><dd>{Municipality}</dd>
<dt>MNRF</dt><dd>{MNRF}</dd>
<dt>Waterbody ID</dt><dd>{WaterbodyID}</dd>
<dt>Fish Species</dt><dd>{Fish Species}</dd>
</dl>
"""
m = folium.Map(location=GTA_COORDINATES, zoom_start=7)
marker_cluster = MarkerCluster().add_to(m)
for eachlake in da:
    k = info_box_template.format(**eachlake)
    iframe = folium.IFrame(html=k, width=500, height=300)
    popup = folium.Popup(iframe, max_width=2650)
    folium.Marker(location = [eachlake['Coords'][0],eachlake['Coords'][1]],
                  popup=popup,
                  icon=folium.Icon(color='blue', icon='cloud'),).add_to(marker_cluster)

display(m)
#folium.Map.save(m, "index.html")
